          Curves  in a family derived from powers of the polar coordinate
          formula  for  ellipses  are found to provide good fits to bound
          orbits  in a range of power-law potentials. This range includes
          the  well-known  $1/r$  (Keplerian) and logarithmic potentials.
          These approximate orbits, called p-ellipses, retain some of the
          basic  geometric  properties  of  ellipses.  They  satisfy  and
