          The  Energetic  X-ray Imaging Survey Telescope (EXIST) is under
          study  for  the  proposed  Black  Hole Finder Probe, one of the
          three   Einstein  Probe  missions  in  NASA's  proposed  Beyond
          Einstein  Program.  EXIST  would  have  unique capabilities: it
          would  survey  the  full sky at 5-600 keV each 95min orbit with
          0.9-5  arcmin, 10microsec - 45min, and ~0.5-5 keV resolution to
          locate  sources  to  10arcsec  and  enable  black  holes  to be
