physics/0602138 [abs, ps, pdf, other] :
          Title: Geometric parametrization of binary elastic collisions
          Authors: Amaro J. Rica da Silva, Jos P. S. Lemos
          Comments: 7 pages, 5 figures
          Subj-class: Classical Physics; Space Physics
          A geometric view of the possible outcomes of elastic collisions
          of  two massive bodies is developed that integrates laboratory,
          center  of  mass, and relative body frames in a single diagram.
          From  these  diagrams  all  the scattering properties of binary
          collisions   can   be   obtained.   The   particular   case  of
          gravitational scattering by a moving massive object corresponds
          to   the  slingshot  maneuver,  and  its  maximum  velocity  is
          obtained.



