          examined  in  the  context  of  the  recent  models of cooling,
          fragmenting clouds building up the baryonic mass of the Galaxy.
          582  high-velocity  clouds  (HVCs) are defined as the potential
          infalling,  condensed  clouds  and  the  sample's  spatial  and
