          with  accretion disks around compact objects. These frequencies
          arise  from  persistent  rotating patterns in the disk that are
          finite in radial extent and driven purely by the gravity of the
          central  body.  Their existence depends on general relativistic
          corrections  to  orbital motion and, if observed, could be used
          to probe the strong gravity region around a black hole. We also
