          velocity  dispersion  but  located near the cluster centre. For
          the  total  metallicity,  Z/H, no significant gradient is found
          (2+/-3%  larger at R_200 than in the core). The cluster-centric
          age  and  alpha/Fe  gradients  are  in  the  sense  expected if
          galaxies  in the cluster core were accreted at an earlier epoch
          than  those  at  larger  radii,  and  if this earlier accretion
          contributed to an earlier cessation of star formation. The size
          of  the  observed  age  trend is comparable to predictions from
