          outburst  with  XMM-Newton on March 20, 2003, and with position
          18h12m27.8s,  -18  12  34  (J2000, approximate positional error
          2"). No known source is present at this position and the source
          was not detected during published ROSAT or ASCA observations of
          that  region.  However,  the  source  may  be  associated  with
          1H1812-182  detected  by HEAO 1, although the error bars on the
          HEAO  1  position are very large and the two sources could also
          be    unrelated.   Therefore,   we   name   the   source   XMMU
