          the  All-Sky  Monitor  (ASM)  on-board  the  Rossi X-ray Timing
          Explorer,  however, reprocessing of the ASM data shows that the
          source  was  in  fact  detected  and it was active for about 50
          days.  The  X-ray  spectrum of this transient is fitted equally
          well by an absorbed power-law (with a spectral index of 2.5) or
          multi-colour  disk  blackbody model (with kT ~ 2 keV), where we
          find   that  the  source  is  highly  absorbed.  We  detect  an
