          shortest  spin  period  millisecond pulsar (MSP) Ter5-ad in the
          globular  cluster  Terzan 5, I also point out a new explanation
          for possible minimum spin periods, P, of MSPs without requiring
          gravitational  radiation  (or  other) slow-down torques. If the
          accretion  of  matter  required  to  spinup  a MSP also reduces
          (buries)  the  neutron star (NS) magnetic field, B, as commonly
          believed,  an inverse correlation between neutron star mass, M,
          and  B is expected together with a positive correlation between
          P  and  B.  Both  are  suggested  for  the  4 MSPs with NS mass
          measures reported (Latimer and Prakash 2004, Science, 304, 536)
