          Observatory  of  bright  Compton  thick  active galactic nuclei
          (AGNs),  those with column densities in excess of 1.5 x 10^{24}
          cm^{-2}  along  the  lines  of  sight.  We  therefore  view the
          powerful   central  engines  only  indirectly,  even  at  X-ray
          energies.  Using  high  spatial resolution and considering only
          galaxies  that  do  not  contain  circumnuclear  starbursts, we
          reveal   the  variety  of  emission  AGNs  alone  may  produce.
