          in  reflection in each case. The only hard X-ray feature is the
          prominent  Fe  K alpha fluorescence line, with equivalent width
          greater  than  1  keV  in  all  sources. The Fe line luminosity
          provides  the  best X-ray indicator of the unseen intrinsic AGN
          luminosity.  In  detail,  the morphologies of the extended soft
          X-ray  emission and optical line emission are similar, and line
          emission  dominates  the soft X-ray spectra. Thus, we attribute
          the  soft  X-ray  emission to material that the central engines
