          that  a  three-band  X-ray  diagnostic  can  correctly classify
          Compton  thick  AGNs,  even  when  significant  soft X-ray line
          emission  is  present.  The  active  nuclei produce most of the
          galaxies'  total observed emission over a broad spectral range,
