          dust,  and  a  continuous component from 5 to 8 microns that in
          most cases comprises an excess above the photosphere throughout
          our  spectral  range.  There  is  considerable variation in the
          silicate  feature/continuum  ratio, which implies variations of
          inclination,  disk flaring, and stellar mass accretion rate. In
          most  of  our stars, structure in the silicate feature suggests
          the presence of a crystalline component. In one, CoKu Tau/4, no
