          2.5+/-0.1x10^9  Msun  (assuming  an 18 Mpc distance). The HI is
          centered  on  NGC 1602 but appears to have two tidal tails, one
          of  which crosses over NGC 1596. The HI located at the position
          of  NGC  1596  has a velocity gradient in the same sense as the
          ionized  gas,  i.e.  opposite to the stellar rotation. Both the
          existence of a large gas reservoir and the velocity gradient of
          the  HI  and  the ionized gas strongly suggest that the ionized
          gas in NGC 1596 originated from NGC 1602.
