          example  where  the  presence  of  counter-rotating  gas can be
          directly  linked to an accretion event. After the accretion has
          stopped  or  the  merging is complete, NGC 1596 may evolve to a
          system  with  more extended counter-rotating gas but no obvious
          signature  of interaction. There is a substantial local HI peak
          in  one  of  the  two tails, where we also find a faint stellar
          counterpart.  The M_HI/L_B ratio in this region is too high for
          a  normal  dwarf elliptical or a low surface brightness galaxy,
