          We  have  identified a binary companion to (42355) 2002 CR46 in
          our ongoing deep survey using the Hubble Space Telescope's High
          Resolution Camera. It is the first companion to be found around
          an  object  in  a non-resonant orbit that crosses the orbits of
          giant  planets.  Objects  in orbits of this kind, the Centaurs,
          have  experienced  repeated  strong scattering with one or more
          giant  planets  and  therefore the survival of binaries in this
          transient   population   has  been  in  question.  Monte  Carlo
