          We  present spectroscopic redshifts for the first 466 X-ray and
          radio-selected AGN targets in the 2 deg^2 COSMOS field. Spectra
          were obtained with the IMACS instrument on the Magellan (Baade)
          telescope,  using  the nod-and-shuffle technique. We identify a
          variety  of Type 1 and Type 2 AGN, as well as red galaxies with
          no  emission  lines. Our redshift yield is 72% down to i_AB=24,
          although   the  yield  is  >90%  for  i_AB<22.  We  expect  the
