          preliminary  measurements  of  their  effective temperature and
          surface  gravity  that  placed them inside or near the known ZZ
          Ceti  instability  strip. We also report detection limits for a
          number  of  DA white dwarfs that showed no sign of variability.
          Finally,  we  revisit  the  ZZ  Ceti  star G232-38 for which we
