          camera is used in parallel to sense speckle images at a spatial
          resolution of lambda/D and at a temporal frequency greater than
          that of atmospheric fluctuations. The MEMS mirror-array is used
          as  an  active  shutter  to  feed speckle images above a preset
          intensity threshold to the spectrometer, thereby increasing the
          signal-to-noise  ratio  (SNR)  of  the spectrogram. Preliminary
          calculations  suggests  an SNR improvement of a factor of about
          1.4. Computer simulations have shown an SNR improvement of 1.1,
          but have not yet fully explored the parameter space.


   
astro-ph/0606182 [abs, ps, pdf, other] :
          Title:  Interferometric  Observations  of  Explosive Variables:
