          IRAS11101-5928   and   the   associated   Herbig-Haro   objects
          HH135/HH136 are presented. The observations reveal the presence
          of  a  well-collimated, parsec-sized H$_2$ outflow with a total
          H$_2$ luminosity of about $2L_\odot$. The bulk of the molecular
          gas is characterized by a ro-vibrational excitation temperature
          of $2000\pm200$ K. A small fraction (0.3%) of the molecular gas
