          flat-bottomed.  Brightness  at  maximum  and  minimum have been
          rather  stable  over  the  years  but  the  light  curve is not
          perfectly  repetitive  or  smooth and small variations exist at
          all  phases.  We  confirm that the star is redder when fainter.
