          We  have  observed the bipolar post-AGB candidate OH 231.8+4.2,
          using  the  mid-infrared  interferometer  MIDI and the infrared
          camera  with  the adaptive optics system NACO on the Very Large
          Telescope.  An  unresolved  core (<200 mas in FWHM) is found at
          the  center  of  the OH 231.8+4.2 in the 3.8 micron image. This
