          efficient.  Our  results show that Toomre instability parameter
          is  less  than  one  everywhere on the $\beta$-disk which means
          that in such disks gravitational instabilities can be occurred,
          so  the  $\beta$-disk  model  can  be  a good candidate for the
          origin   of  planetary  systems.  Our  results  show  that  the
          $\beta$-disks will decouple in the outer part of the disk where
