          the  radio  bubbles appear to overlap with filaments of H_alpha
          emission.  The  high-resolution  observations  reveal a compact
          source, likely to be associated with the nucleus of the galaxy,
          and  a  possible  radio  jet  towards  the  south-west. We have
          compiled  a  representative  sample of galaxies with bubbles of
          non-thermal  radio  emission  and  find that these are found in
          galaxies with an AGN.
