          [NII]  emission  lines  from DensePak and the H-beta and [OIII]
          emission  from  Sauron  allow  the  construction  of diagnostic
          diagrams  that  highlight the transition from star formation in
          the  nuclear ring to excitation by high-velocity shocks or by a
          central  AGN  towards the center. DensePak measurements for the
