          dust  extinction  using  the Balmer decrement, results in rates
          which are consistent with those estimated from the far-infrared
          luminosity.  The  majority  (>60%)  of our sample show spectral
          features  characteristic  of  AGN,  with  ~65% exhibiting broad
          Balmer  emission  lines.  A  proportion  of  these sources show
          relatively  low [OIII]/H_beta line ratios, which are similar to
