          show  an  excess of [OIII] emission, by a factor of 5-10 times,
          relative   to   the  hard  X-ray  luminosity  compared  to  the
          correlation  between  these two properties seen in Seyferts and
          QSOs  locally.  From  our spectral diagnostics, we propose that
          the strong [OIII] emission in these galaxies arises from shocks
          in  dense  gaseous  regions  in  this  vigorously  star-forming
          population.


   
astro-ph/0607583 [abs, ps, pdf, other] :
          Title:  Evidence for Heating of Neutron Stars by Magnetic Field
