          Authors: Chuang Ren, Eric G. Blackman, Wen-fai Fong
          Comments:  13 pages, including 3 figs., Submitted to Physics of
          Plasmas
          Whether    a    faster-than-Coulomb   collisionless   mechanism
          equilibrates  ion-electron  plasmas  with  ions  initially much
          hotter  than electrons is a fundamental plasma physics question
          and  important  for under standing low-luminosity astrophysical
          accretion  flows.  Here  we  study whether Weibel instabilities
          driven   by   proton  temperature  anisotropy  produce  such  a
          mechanism.
