          several  simple geometrical configurations and their dependence
          on  the  main  input parameters. Overall, we find line profiles
          reaching  from  doubly  peaked  symmetric emission to symmetric
          Voigt  (absorption)  in  static  configurations with increasing
          dust content, and asymmetric red-(blue-) shifted emission lines
          with  a  blue  (red)  counterpart  ranging  from  absorption to
          emission (with increasing line/continuum strength) in expanding
          (infalling) media.
