          absorption  line  observations from these astrophysical sources
          and   gamma-ray   burst  afterglows  using  simple  theoretical
          estimates   of   spectral  line  absorption  cross-section  and
          emissivity  accounting  for  major  processes  populating upper
          hyperfine sublevel. Using modern and near-future instruments it
          appears  possible  both  to observe absorption line of 14-N VII
          (rest  wavelength  5.652  mm)  from  the warm-hot intergalactic
          medium  and  galactic  halos  at  redshifts  above  z=0.15  and
          emission lines of several less abundant isotopes from young and
          middle-aged supernova remnants.



