          CLOVER  is  an experiment which aims to detect the signature of
          gravitational  waves  from  inflation  by  measuring the B-mode
          polarization   of   the  cosmic  microwave  background.  CLOVER
          consists of three telescopes operating at 97, 150, and 220 GHz.
