          Title: Optical and Infrared Emission from the AXPs and SGRs
          Authors: Unal Ertan, Sirin Caliskan
          Comments: 12 pages, accepted for publication in ApJ Letters
          We  show  that  the irradiated accretion disk model can account
          for  all the optical and infrared observations of the anomalous
          X-ray  pulsars  in  the  persistent  state.  Model  fits do not
          constrain the outer disk radii, while placing an upper limit to
          the  inner  disk  radii, and thus to the strength of the dipole
          component  of the stellar magnetic field. While magnetar fields
