          Title:   On   the   age   of  the  TW  Hydrae  Association  and
          2M1207334-393254
          Authors: David Barrado y Navascues
          Comments: Astronomy & Astrophysics, accepted
          We  have  estimated the age of the young moving group TW Hydrae
          Association,  a  cohort  of  a few dozen stars and brown dwarfs
          located  near the Sun which share the same kinematic properties
          and,  presumably,  the  same origin and age. The chronology has
          been  determined by analyzing different properties (magnitudes,
          colors,  activity,  lithium)  of its members and comparing them
          with several well-known star forming regions and open clusters,
          as   well   as   theoretical  models.  In  addition,  by  using
