astro-ph/0608637 [abs, ps, pdf, other] :
          Title:  The structure of dark matter halos: self-similar models
          versus N-body simulations
          Authors: Leonid Chuzhoy
          Comments: 3 pages, 3 figures
          We derive the density profile of cold dark matter halos using a
          self-similar accretion model. We show that if the clumpiness of
          the  infalling  matter  is  taken  into account, then the inner
          density  slope, d(log{rho})/d(log{r}), is close to -1. Compared
          with  the  density  profiles  predicted  by different numerical
          simulations,  we  find that outside ~0.1% of the virial radius,
          our  solutions  agree best with the fitting formula proposed by
          Navarro  et al. (2004), d(ln{rho})/d(ln{r})=-2(r/R)^0.17, where
          R  is a characteristic radius, inside which the density profile
          becomes shallower than isothermal.


   
